The paper deals with the analysis of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the estimation of Lipschitz bounds, which is a topic in optimization (cs.IT) and analysis (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a nonlinear discriminant analysis, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
